title.narrative: 2.1 STRENGTHENED PARTNERSHIPS

description.narrative: Strengthened partnerships, policy, planning, governance, capacity and accountability of education authorities to deliver quality pre-primary and basic education (Grades 1-10) for all children (ages 5-18) in Jordan., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Increased number of children aged 5-18 access quality inclusive early and basic education in a child-friendly and protective environment.

description.narrative: In line with Education Sector Plan (ESP) (2018-2022) and Education During Emergency Plan (2020/2022), UNICEF supported the education sector to respond to school closures by enabling vulnerable children to have continued access to education and advocating for safe school reopening. UNICEF supported MoE to reimagine education through the design and implementation of innovative learning recovery programmes, including Learning Bridges, blended teacher professional development, and a focus on school leadership. UNICEF ensured that investments support long-term resilience and quality of education, including transition of the NFE and the Nashatati life skills programmes from UNICEF-funded NGO delivery to MoE implementation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
